 {"id":"br-r37-c1-9m2vs","title":"parity: Graph constructor silently drops edges from dict-of-list adjacency input","description":"fnx.Graph({0: [1], 1: [0, 2], 2: [1]}) returns a graph with 3 nodes and 0 edges. nx.Graph(...) correctly parses it as adjacency-list, returning 3 nodes and 2 edges. _decode_dict_of_dicts_into handles dict-of-DICT shape but skips when the value is a list (continue at 'if not isinstance(nbrs, dict)'). Drop-in code that builds a graph from a dict-of-list adjacency representation gets a wrong graph silently. Same pre-existing pattern from br-r37-c1-lc3em (dict-of-dict input was originally handled, but list-of-neighbours was not). Fix: extend _decode_dict_of_dicts_into to also handle the dict-of-list case (and dict-of-set/tuple by iterating any iterable of neighbour nodes).","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-26T08:48:21.921012966Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-26T08:53:41.082780910Z","closed_at":"2026-04-26T08:53:41.080770904Z","close_reason":"Fixed in commit ca5cc1f. Graph/DiGraph/MultiGraph/MultiDiGraph constructors now accept dict-of-list (and any iterable-valued dict) adjacency input matching nx.from_dict_of_lists. 11 parity tests freeze the contract.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"br-r37-c1-9mdsv","title":"parity: label_propagation_communities return type drift","description":"fnx.label_propagation_communities(G) returns dict_values([{0,1,2},...]) — a dict_values view object — while networkx returns a generator yielding sets. Drop-in code that does isinstance(result, types.GeneratorType) or relies on consuming once will diverge. Convert wrapper to yield sets directly (return iter(...)). File: python/franken_networkx/__init__.py (around line 17175).","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-25T05:05:05.214287589Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T05:08:52.048798239Z","closed_at":"2026-04-25T05:08:52.046958637Z","close_reason":"Invalid: NetworkX 3.6.1 and legacy oracle both return dict_values; existing wrapper and tests already match.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"br-r37-c1-9yavb","title":"parity: utils.heaps {BinaryHeap, MinHeap, PairingHeap} + classes.function.frozen (4 surfaces)","description":"Two missing utility surfaces: networkx.utils.heaps exposes BinaryHeap, MinHeap, PairingHeap classes used as the default heap= kwarg in stoer_wagner and other algorithms; networkx.classes.function exposes frozen as a no-op exception-raising sentinel attached to frozen graphs by nx.freeze. franken_networkx surfaces neither. Add Python wrappers re-exporting these directly from nx (no graph-conversion needed; they are pure utilities).","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-04-25T23:09:42.538123502Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T23:24:40.588218288Z","closed_at":"2026-04-25T23:24:40.586349930Z","close_reason":"Shipped in 63cc1d9: BinaryHeap/MinHeap/PairingHeap re-exports + frozen sentinel. Verified BinaryHeap insert/min/pop, PairingHeap insert/min, frozen() raises NetworkXError as expected.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
+{"id":"br-r37-c1-bf1wb","title":"parity: has_eulerian_path raises NotImplemented on directed graphs; nx accepts directed","description":"fnx.has_eulerian_path(DiGraph) raises NetworkXNotImplemented('not implemented for directed type'). nx supports both directed and undirected — a directed graph has an Eulerian path iff at most one vertex has (out_degree - in_degree) = 1, at most one has -1, all others 0, AND the underlying undirected graph is connected. fnx.is_eulerian on directed graphs already works correctly; only has_eulerian_path is over-restricted. Drop-in code that calls has_eulerian_path(digraph) breaks. Fix: delegate to nx for directed inputs (or add native directed support).","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-26T09:40:11.094534431Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-26T09:42:05.327792721Z","closed_at":"2026-04-26T09:42:05.325878577Z","close_reason":"Fixed in commit 8fe2bcb. has_eulerian_path now accepts directed graphs (delegating to nx for the directed case), matching nx's full contract. 10 parity tests freeze the contract.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"br-r37-c1-bj91d","title":"parity: random_uniform_k_out_graph + reverse_cuthill_mckee_ordering + flow_matrix_row missing (3 utilities)","description":"Three nx utilities not surfaced by franken_networkx: random_uniform_k_out_graph(n, k, self_loops=True, with_replacement=True, seed=None) from generators.directed (k-out random digraph), reverse_cuthill_mckee_ordering(G, heuristic=None) from utils (bandwidth reduction node ordering), and flow_matrix_row(G, weight=None, dtype=float, solver=lu) from algorithms.centrality.flow_matrix (current-flow centrality kernel). Add Python wrappers via _call_networkx_submodule_for_parity, export at top-level, add to __all__.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-04-25T21:11:43.252663714Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T21:32:49.845701550Z","closed_at":"2026-04-25T21:32:49.843812193Z","close_reason":"Shipped in e3f2e78: random_uniform_k_out_graph + reverse_cuthill_mckee_ordering + flow_matrix_row wrappers. Verified n=8 k=2 seed=42 nodes/edges match, P8 RCM ordering match, K4 flow_matrix_row count match nx.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"br-r37-c1-cirha","title":"parity: 34 top-level functions accept positional args that nx made keyword-only","description":"fnx's signatures use POSITIONAL_OR_KEYWORD for params nx declares as KEYWORD_ONLY (after *). Affected: dfs_edges/dfs_tree/dfs_predecessors/dfs_successors/dfs_postorder_nodes/dfs_preorder_nodes (sort_neighbors), random_spanning_tree/random_labeled_tree/random_unlabeled_tree/random_labeled_rooted_tree/random_unlabeled_rooted_tree/random_unlabeled_rooted_forest (seed, multiplicative, number_of_*), connected_watts_strogatz_graph/dense_gnm_random_graph/duplication_divergence_graph/gnm_random_graph/random_lobster_graph/random_powerlaw_tree/generalized_petersen_graph (create_using), directed_edge_swap (nswap, max_tries, seed), from_numpy_array (nodelist), harmonic_diameter (weight), identified_nodes (store_contraction_as), number_of_spanning_trees (weight, root), subgraph_view (filter_node, filter_edge). Forward-compat issue: code using positional form on fnx breaks when ported to nx. Fix: insert * before the documented keyword-only params in each wrapper.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-26T05:36:02.353496302Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-26T05:40:25.924391077Z","closed_at":"2026-04-26T05:40:25.922533471Z","close_reason":"Fixed in commit 863a001. 25 functions now match nx's POSITIONAL_OR_KEYWORD vs KEYWORD_ONLY param kinds. Code using positional form for these params now correctly raises TypeError on both fnx and nx, preventing forward-compat foot-guns. number_of_spanning_trees got a Python wrapper around the Rust binding. 31 parity tests freeze the contract.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"br-r37-c1-cujmq","title":"parity: VF2 GraphMatcher/DiGraphMatcher/MultiGraphMatcher classes missing","description":"networkx.algorithms.isomorphism exposes GraphMatcher, DiGraphMatcher, MultiGraphMatcher, MultiDiGraphMatcher classes for the classical VF2 algorithm with rich API: subgraph_is_isomorphic(), subgraph_isomorphisms_iter(), match(), candidate_pairs_iter(), semantic_feasibility(), syntactic_feasibility(), initialize(). fnx exposes only the top-level functions (is_isomorphic, vf2pp_*) but no Matcher classes. Add wrapper classes that delegate to nx.algorithms.isomorphism via _networkx_graph_for_parity, exporting as fnx.GraphMatcher etc.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"cod-networkx","created_at":"2026-04-25T07:30:43.669346473Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T09:18:29.924704555Z","closed_at":"2026-04-25T09:18:29.922845114Z","close_reason":"Completed in 742c813","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
